    What's special

    Spacious propertyNatural ResourcesEconomic OpportunitiesProsperous AgricultureDiverse communityNatural HVAC systeM
    This plot of land is a truly unique opportunity for settlers seeking wealth, connections, or just a tolerant community. Perfectly positioned along the beautiful southeastern coast of North America, this land boasts fertile soil, majestic rivers, and dense forests. If you happen to love farming, or just want to be on the cutting edge of colonial expansion, you ought to find yourself a new home in the great colony of Georgia.
    What the owner loves about this home
    Located along the southeastern coastline, this lovely landscape offers fertile land that's many lucrative agriculture endeavors. If you've got a knack for growing cotton, tobacco, rice, or indigo, consider yourself in luck! Thanks to nearby rivers and lush forests, you can enjoy the ample resources and stay productive year-round.

    Georgia doesn't just have farming to offer though. One quick move to the south and you gain the honor of protecting the colonies. Due to Georgia's strategic position above Florida, you and your neighbors get the privilege of dealing with any pesky Spanish colonists. Defend our trade route access, or die trying!

    Speaking of your neighbors, you are one purchase away from finding yourself in a diverse and thriving community. Immigrants are practically flooding in from a variety of regions including the British Isles, northern Europe, the Mediterranean, Africa, the Caribbean, and a host of our very own colonies. (Please note that there are a few squatters who like to claim they own the land, just ignore them).

    If you happen to like your religion, then this land is getting even more perfect for you (unless you're Catholic). Come on down to Georgia, where we are accepting and welcoming to a multitude of religions (not Roman Catholicism). It doesn't matter if you're Anglican, Lutheran, Moravian, Methodist, or Jewish, Georgia is the right place for you (It matters if you're Catholic). We are all like family after all!

    So if this property sound of interest to you, sail on over, join our growing population, and we'll get you set up to live out the rest of your days as an indentured servant, or something else.
